<div id="pf5f" class="pf w2 h3e" data-page-no="5f"><div class="pc pc5f w2 h3e"><div class="t m29b x34 h1a ya41 ff2 fs12 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Overshadowing Providence </div><div class="t m77 xa4 h1a yb10 ff2 fs12 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0"></div><div class="t m116 xce h1a ya41 ff2 fs12 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">March 30 </div><div class="t m21f x26 h17 yafb ff1 fs9 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">10. Read 2 Samuel 22:35-43 in light of the principles of the great </div><div class="t m12e x20 h17 y106 ff1 fs9 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">controversy between Christ and Satan. (See Rev. 12:1-17.) How </div><div class="t m12c x20 h17 yafc ff1 fs9 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">would you explain the following? </div><div class="t m198 x27 h18 yafe ff5 fs9 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">&quot;He teaches my hands to make war&quot; (2 Sam. 22:35, NKJV; see Eph. </div><div class="t m254 x26 h18 yb11 ff5 fs9 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">6:10-17). </div><div class="t m5da x11 h18 yb12 ff5 fs9 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">&quot;You have subdued . . . those who rose against me&quot; (2 Sam. 22:40, </div><div class="t m273 x26 h18 y54d ff5 fs9 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">NKJV; see Rev. 12:9-11). </div><div class="t m4d8 x11 h18 y93c ff5 fs9 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">&quot;I beat them as fine as the dust of the earth&quot; (2 Sam. 22:43, NKJV; </div><div class="t m276 x28 h18 y552 ff5 fs9 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">see Ps. 2:8, 9; Rev. 19:15). </div><div class="t m237 xcd h19 yaa ff2 fs11 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">WED </div><div class="t m620 x28 h17 y555 ff1 fs9 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">11. Summarize in your own words some of the reasons David had </div><div class="t m273 x2c h17 y2b8 ff1 fs9 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">for being grateful: </div><div class="t m367 x55 h18 y2b9 ff5 fs9 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">2 Sam. 22:20, 44 </div><div class="t m77 xa5 h18 y2b9 ff5 fs9 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0"></div><div class="t mec xa9 h18 y2b9 ff5 fs9 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0"> </div><div class="t m3d8 x55 h18 yb13 ff5 fs9 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Verses 26-28 </div><div class="t m77 x29 h18 yb13 ff5 fs9 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0"></div><div class="t mec xa9 h18 yb13 ff5 fs9 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0"> </div><div class="t m325 x55 h18 yb14 ff5 fs9 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Verses 29-31 </div><div class="t m77 x29 h18 y2bd ff5 fs9 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0"></div><div class="t mec xa9 h18 y2bd ff5 fs9 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0"> </div><div class="t m23d x55 h18 yb15 ff5 fs9 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Verses 36, 37 </div><div class="t m77 x29 h18 yb15 ff5 fs9 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0"></div><div class="t mec xa9 h18 yb15 ff5 fs9 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0"> </div><div class="t m25f x55 h18 yb16 ff5 fs9 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Verses 50, 51 </div><div class="t m77 x29 h18 yb16 ff5 fs9 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0"></div><div class="t mec xa9 h18 yb16 ff5 fs9 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0"> </div><div class="t m2dd xa h18 yb17 ff5 fs9 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Deitrich Bonhoeffer, who spent the last years of his life in a Nazi prison </div><div class="t m24a xe h18 y120 ff5 fs9 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">camp and eventually became a martyr, loved and read the psalms daily. A </div><div class="t m395 xe h18 y121 ff5 fs9 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">friend who was with him in his last days said that he seemed to diffuse </div><div class="t m551 xe h18 y122 ff5 fs9 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">happiness and joy to those about him, and manifested a deep sense of grati-</div><div class="t m2a9 xe h18 yb18 ff5 fs9 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">tude over just being alive. He had learned well the lesson of the psalmist: </div><div class="t m3af xe h18 y124 ff5 fs9 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">gratitude born of adversity sings God&apos;s praises from the heart, not just with </div><div class="t m162 xe h18 yb19 ff5 fs9 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">the lips. </div><div class="t m1a1 xe h17 y2c4 ff1 fs9 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">IV. DAVID THE PROPHET (2 Sam. 23:1-7). </div><div class="t mc1 xe h17 yb1a ff1 fs9 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">12. </div><div class="t m5f1 x55 h17 yb1a ff1 fs9 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">What New Testament criteria confirms David&apos;s prophetic gift? </div><div class="t m3ee x55 h17 yb1b ff1 fs9 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Who was the &quot;Rock of Israel&quot; who spoke to him (2 Sam. 23:1-</div><div class="t m25e x55 h17 y12a ff1 fs9 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">3)? 2 Peter 1:21; 1 Cor. 10:4. </div><div class="t mc1 xe h17 yb0e ff1 fs9 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">13. </div><div class="t m415 x55 h17 yb0e ff1 fs9 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Study the following sampling of the prophecies made by David </div><div class="t m103 x55 h17 y2cc ff1 fs9 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">about the Messiah to come. Compare their New Testament fulfill-</div><div class="t m3af x55 h17 yb1c ff1 fs9 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">ment. </div><div class="t m229 x3f h17 yb1d ff1 fs9 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">95 </div></div><div class="pi" data-data='{"ctm":[1.000000,0.000000,0.000000,1.000000,0.000000,0.000000]}'></div></div>
